DISASTER NOTICE: SCHOOL START DATE DELAYED
With heavy hearts, we will delay the start of the school year until Monday, August 31, due to the substantial damage caused by the storm this week. We will still have a two hour early dismissal on Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday of that week. Also as a reminder, we will NOT have a late start on the morning of Monday, August 31 because of the early dismissal.
Thanks,
Baxter CSD Admin

July 23 at 12:00 PM ·

Are you interested in becoming a Substitute Teacher? Register now for a remote learning course! Learn more at http://ow.ly/q7vA50zA9Hi

The degree requirement to obtain a substitute authorization is changed from a bachelor’s degree to an associate’s degree or 60 semester hours through a regionally-accredited institution. The substitute authorization course is still required. All courses are online for a total of 20 hours. Choose any course that fits with your schedule!

The pitcher moved up on the mound and threw him way more than three strikes until he eventually hit the ball and got on base. The Baxter dugout cheered just as loud as ours did. Baxter – you were truly a display of good sportsmanship – which is exactly what our world needs right now. Thank you!

post_text:
Dear Baxter Families,
I am sure many of you have already heard the announcement, but for those of you who haven't yet heard, the governor has officially closed all Iowa schools for the rest of the school year. We will continue with our voluntary learning opportunities and we strongly encourage students to take advantage of them. As we get more information from the Iowa Department of Education and the Governor's office we will update you. Also all spring sports and activities have been cancelled and we will find out by June 1st about summer activities.

This is very disappointing news and I hope all of our Baxter families know how much we miss all of you and how saddened we are by the news that we don't get to come back and finish our school year together. Over the next few days we will be sending out more detailed information about things like collecting things from your desk or lockers and plans for events like graduation. In the meantime, I hope everyone continues to stay safe and we look forward to hopefully seeing you all in the fall.

Take care,
Dr. Clapper

COVID 19 UPDATE: SCHOOL CLOSED THROUGH APRIL 30.
Dear Baxter Families,
The governor announced today that all schools in Iowa will be closed through April 30. She also told us that by April 16th she would give districts direction about school closures into May. As soon as we know any updates, we will pass them along. Until then take care of yourselves and your families. We miss seeing all of you and we can't wait until we can get our lives back to normal, but until then, stay safe.
Take care,
Dr. Clapper

post_text:
COVID 19: DAILY, 10 AM UPDATE:
Dear Baxter Students, Parents, and Families:

Today is a good day to have a great day! We hope all of you wake up with a plan and a purpose today.

Please remember that people will be at the school on Monday to help students get things like, chromebooks, instruments, and medicine. If you feel you need anything specific be sure and e-mail your principal. rluther@baxter.k12.ia.is or jaker@baxter.k12.ia.us

I share this term with our football team frequently: "Control the Controllables". We are living in a time where we are feeling what we can control is becoming less and less. I would argue the controllables are always the same; attitude, passion, focus, commitment, etc. We make those decisions every day. Inky Johnson is a former football player who now does motivational speaking. I hope you click the link and really listen to his message.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JvmrQV9JAcQ

Baxter Community Schools

Class of 2020: Check out the Last Dollar Scholarship

We want to make families aware of a great scholarship opportunity for high school seniors. The Last Dollar Scholarship is a state-funded program that pays tuition and mandatory fees for hundreds of programs offered through Iowa’s community colleges. All students need to do is complete a FAFSA and enroll as a full-time student in the fall. For more information, visit www.iowacollegeaid.gov/LastDollar.

post_text:
SCHOOL BOARD MEETINGS:
Baxter school board meeting nights have been moved to Wednesday nights, 6 pm, effective immediately.
Board meetings will now take place on the third Wednesday of every month at 6:00 pm unless otherwise noted. This allows for board members to attend more school functions, principals, who are also coaches, to attend board meetings, and allow for parents and community members to attend board meetings, who otherwise may be attending activities on Monday evenings, if they so choose. The next regular board meeting is Wednesday, November 20, 2019, 6 pm, in the city/school library.
